Filtering BAWR

Filtering of BAWR using both vcftools.

Starting with populations.snps.vcf that came from m3M2n2 denovo assembly and populations run that included all individuals except some tossed based on poor gstacks.log.distribs. Individuals are in BAWR_whitelist_n76.

Use VCFtools to calc basic stats

source ~/.bash_profile
myvcf=populations.snps.vcf
mkdir all_data_stats
vcftools --vcf $myvcf --out all_data_stats/all.snps --missing-indv
vcftools --vcf $myvcf --out all_data_stats/all.snps --depth
vcftools --vcf $myvcf --out all_data_stats/all.snps --site-mean-depth
vcftools --vcf $myvcf --out all_data_stats/all.snps --missing-site

Set-up R function for visualizing these stats

library(ggplot2)
library(patchwork)
suppressMessages(library(dplyr))

plot.vcf.stats <- function(prfx){
  adat  <- read.delim(paste(prfx, ".imiss", sep=""), sep = "\t", header=TRUE)
  a <- ggplot(adat, aes(F_MISS)) + 
      geom_histogram(fill="orange", col="black", alpha=0.6,
                   binwidth=0.05, show.legend=FALSE) + 
      xlim(0.0, 1.0) + ggtitle("FREQ SITES MISSING PER INDIVIDUAL")
  
  bdat  <- read.delim(paste(prfx, ".idepth", sep=""), sep = "\t", header=TRUE)
  b <- ggplot(bdat, aes(MEAN_DEPTH)) + 
      geom_histogram(fill="dodgerblue", col="black", alpha=0.6,
                   binwidth=1, show.legend=FALSE) + 
      xlim(0,30) + ggtitle("MEAN DEPTH PER INDV ACROSS LOCI")
  
  cdat  <- read.delim(paste(prfx, ".lmiss", sep=""), sep = "\t", header=TRUE)
  c <- ggplot(cdat, aes(F_MISS)) + 
      geom_histogram(fill="orange", col="black", alpha=0.6,
                   binwidth=0.05, show.legend=FALSE) + 
      xlim(0.0, 1.0) + ggtitle("FREQ SITES MISSING PER LOCUS")
  
  ddat  <- read.delim(paste(prfx, ".ldepth.mean", sep=""), sep = "\t", header=TRUE)
  d <- ggplot(ddat, aes(MEAN_DEPTH)) + 
      geom_histogram(fill="dodgerblue", col="black", alpha=0.6,
                   binwidth=1, show.legend=FALSE) + 
      xlim(0,30) + ggtitle("MEAN DEPTH PER LOCUS ACROSS INDIVIDUAL")
  
  #options(repr.plot.width=18, repr.plot.height=12)
  print ((a | b) / 
      (c | d))
}

Do first cuts of missing data.

  1. Convert low depth sites to missing data. Very generious MinDP 2, MaxDP 20
  2. Only keep variable sites (MAC=2)
  3. Visualize
mkdir n75_data_DPmac
vcftools --vcf n75_data_stats/bawr_n75.snps.vcf  \
    --minDP 2 \
    --maxDP 20 \
    --mac 2 \
    --recode --recode-INFO-all \
    --out n75_data_DPmac/n75_data_DPmac.snps

Filter for missingness and mean-depth

Filter first for missingness. 70% cutoff seems reasonable for now since most individuals have a high level of missingness.

mkdir n75_data_DPmac_L70mDP3

vcftools --vcf n75_data_DPmac/n75_data_DPmac.snps.vcf \
  --max-missing 0.70 \
  --min-meanDP 3 \
  --max-meanDP 15 \
  --recode --recode-INFO-all \
  --out n75_data_DPmac_L70mDP3/n75_data_DPmac_L70mDP3.snps
  
mv n75_data_DPmac_L70mDP3/n75_data_DPmac_L70mDP3.snps.recode.vcf \
  n75_data_DPmac_L70mDP3/n75_data_DPmac_L70mDP3.snps.vcf
